deck: Buffy and Cordelia compete for the title of Homecoming Queen.
description:
Scott breaks up with Buffy the day after asking her to the Homecoming dance because he senses she isn't focused on him, which is correct as she's secretly nursing her old boyfriend Angel back to health.

Buffy learns that her favorite teacher does not remember her, and that Cordelia didn't tell her about the yearbook photo day as she was supposed to, Buffy decides to compete with her for the Homecoming Queen title.

Meanwhile, Mr. Trick announces a competition called "SlayerFest '98", wherein a group of supernatural types will compete to kill the slayers.
name: Homecoming

description: Clark discovers that Kara sent messages from Krypton in the past that indicate that Brainiac wants to kill baby Kal-El so Clark will not exist in the future. Clark is torn because he thinks the world would be better off if he had never arrived in Smallville so Jor-El arranges for Clark to see what life would have been like if he hadn't existed.
name: Apocalypse

description: Clark desperately searches for Kara and Brainiac, as Brainiac is the only one who can reverse Lana's condition. Clark asks Chloe to check any large power surges in the area, so she breaks into several government computers, setting off alarms. Jimmy is caught between the Department of Domestic Security - who threatens him with jail unless he helps them arrest Chloe - and Lex, who offers to help clear Chloe if Jimmy agrees to be in his debt.
name: Sleeper

description: The secret of Veritas leads Lex in a dangerous directionthat puts Clark and Lex in each other's crosshairs.
name: Descent

description: Kara decides to teach Clark how to fly in order to strengthen his chances against Brainiac. However, Brainiac seems to have the upper hand against the super cousins, and some of Clark's loved ones are caught in the crossfire. Lex remembers a memory in which Lionel meets with a secret society.
name: Veritas

description: Lionel arranges to have Clark kidnapped and held in a kryptonite-lined cell at a LuthorCorp facility. After Chloe and Lana find a military electric probe at the farm, they confront Lionel, who throws suspicion onto Lex. Chloe takes Kara to the Fortress and begs Jor-El to restore her memory and her powers as she is the only one who can save Clark.
name: Traveler

description: Kara and Jimmy attend a OneRepublic concert and one of the roadies turns out to be former Smallville resident Pete Ross. Pete unwillingly chews some kryptonite-laced gum and develops streching powers. Clark and Chloe are thrilled to meet up with their old friend but warn him against using his powers in public. However, Lex discovers Pete's powers and blackmails him into helping break into Lionel's safe by threatening to reveal Chloe is a meteor-freak.
name: Hero

description: Lois follows Lex to Detroit and discovers he has found Kara, who has amnesia. A busboy who is obsessed with Kara, fears Lex will take her away, so he shoots Lex and holds Kara and Lois captive. After Lex's comatose body is found, Chloe offers to heal him, but Clark refuses to let her.
name: Fracture

description: While secretly working for Oliver, Chloe intercepts one of Lex's project files, but she is attacked by Black Canary, a mystery woman with a subsonic cry. Dinah Lance, Black Canary's alter ego, is a conservative talk show host who is working at the Daily Planet and clashes with Lois. Lex convinces Black Canary that Green Arrow and his team are terrorists so she launches an attack on Green Arrow and Clark. Meanwhile, Lois discovers Oliver's secret.
name: Siren

description: While Clark is still frozen in the Fortress, Bizarro takes over his life with Lana. Unaware she is with Bizarro, Lana enjoys the "new Clark" and shares information she's gathered on a seriel killer who is draining his victims of all trace minerals. Lex is stunned at Lionel's reaction after Grant reveales he is a clone of Julian.
name: Persona

deck: Tomoki Sakurai finds a mysterious girl with angel wings falling fro the sky and his life was never be the same again.
description:
I do not think I have ever had a dream like this before.

There is a girl in it I have never met.

I love her...

...and she loves me in return.

But... in the end, she always...

The sky always spirits her away and I wake from my dream.

- Tomoki Sakurai

The story starts from a recurring dream that Tomoki has ever since he is little. Why is he having this dream? Could it be a premonition of a grand event or an omen of darker things to come? No one knows.

After the dream sequence, Eishiro Sugata, together with his assistant, Pretty (A doll.) introduces himself to explain a phenomenon he is currently investigating. The matter of interest is a black hole circling on the earth's surface. He believe that this hole is a gateway to a "New World".

Every morning Sohara has taken it upon herself to wake Tomoki up so he would not be late for school like a typical childhood friend. he had trouble waking Tomoki, so she pulls his blanket away from him in hope that he comes to his senses and fully awaken. After pulling his blanket, Sohara found out that another part of Tomoki's body is fully awake. Even though it is not his fault, Tomoki receives the infamous Sohara Chop.

Still groggy from being beaten half to death, Tomoki dress-up and went to school with Sohara. During class, Sohara noticed that Tomoki is about to fall asleep but could not do a thing because of the distance of their sleep. While asleep, Tomoki keeps having the same dream about a woman whose face is hidden and spirited away by the sky as they are about to touch. Tomoki was then woken-up by Sohara and she noticed that he is crying. Concerned for his well-being Sohara suggested that Tomoki consult somebody with regard to his recurring dream and said that he consult with Eishiro Sugata. Tomoki refused because of his weird reputation. Sohara not having the patience to deal with Tomoki's ramblings threatens him with a Sohara Chop.

After being beaten half to death, dress-up and went to school with Sohara. During class, Tomoki finds himself getting sleepy and finally doze off, Sohara saw him and attempts to wake him but could not because of the distance of their seats. Meanwhile Tomoki finds himself in a familiar scene, he is having that dream again, it is still the same, before he could get close to the woman in his dreams, she is spirited away by the sky. Sohara finally woken Tomoki up but finds him in tears and she knew it was that dream again. Concerned for her childhood friends well-being, Sohara suggested that Tomoki consult somebody with his recurring dream and suggested getting the help of Eishito Sugata. Tomoki refused due to Sugata's reputation, but before they can discuss it a commotion erupts outside the school building.

Tomoki and Sohara went outside to see what is causing the disturbance and find a person on the roof of the school building with a Hang-Glider and attempting to to fly, it come to no surprise who it was, it was Eishiro Sugata. Tomoki desperately tried to find someone who can help him talk some sense with Sugata and finds the Student Council President Mikako Satsukitane in the crowd. Tomoki pleaded with her to help since she is also Sugata's childhood freind but all falls in deaf-ears due to her sadistic nature. With no one to stop Sugata, he attempted the filght, it was looking good for a few seconds but alas, he crashed as expected. Sugata was lucky he only sustained minor injuries.

Tomoki and Sohara went to the New World Discovery Club's club room to discuss Tomoki's dream. After a brief lesson on Sugata's New World theory and revealing that the anomaly will come to Sorami City when evening come, Sugata, Sohara, and Tomoki decided to meet at a certain place in the City. Tomoki was reluctant at first but is convinced less suffer a Sohara Chop.

That evening, Tomoki arrived at the designated place but finds himself alone as his companions encountered last minute obstacles. When Tomoki decided to leave, he received a call from Sugata telling him to leave immediately but the signal was interfered by something. A light suddenly come shooting down from the sky and after it hit ground, a large crater was created and inside the crater a girl was lying unconscious. Upon checking, the girl have angel like wings. Suddenly a large pillar-like debris come crashing down, Tomoki flee but thought of the girl's safety and decided to return to help. He tried to pull the girl up but a huge chuck of pillar-like debris is on top of him. When the smoke clears he found himself alive and flying in the air held by the mysterious girl he is about to rescue. The Angel-Like being begins to say "Imprint" and the chain in her choker extended and wrap around Tomoki's wrist. This signifies that she now recognize Tomoki as her master. The girl introduced herself as Ikaros, a Type Alpha Pet Class Angeloid.

The following morning, Tomoki woke-up and finds Ikaros by his side. She explained to Tomoki that she is there to perform his every command. Skeptical, Tomoki wish for money and Ikaros said if One Billion Yen, caught in the moment, Tomoki nod and Ikaros made his wish come true by using a Transport Card. Suddenly, a bundle of cash came crashing down on him. Realizing the power of the device in Ikaros' possession, Tomoki tried different ways to use the card. First, he made himself invisible and came to Sohara's room while changing and fondled her breast. He went outside still invisible and naked streaking his heart-out. With the card he also wished for all the delicious food he could think of. He is practically living the life of a king.It was all well and good until he made a mistake. He wished to rule the world without thinking, to grant this, the card erases every person in existence, when he asked Ikaros what happen, she said that for Tomoki to rule the world, every person must acknowledge him and since no will acknowledge him the card simply erases every one, the card always think of the best logical solution when granting a wish.

Tomoki desperately tried to find a living soul but found none, in his despair, ordered Ikaros to also disappear and the card turned into a gun and Ikaros tried to kill herself per Tomoki's order. Tomoki immediately tried to stop her and wished it was all a bad dream. Morning came and things seems to be all as it seems before his wish. Ikaros explained that Tomoki's last wish supersedes his earlier wish.
name: A Full-frontal Hero Arises in the World!
